---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import TimeLineElement from "../components/cv/TimeLine.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Resume" sideBarActiveItemID="cv">
  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Profile</div>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-10 text-justify">
Christopher R. Hudson is a Senior Research Engineer at the Center for Advanced Vehicular Systems (CAVS) and a Lecturer in the Department of Computer Science and Engineering at Mississippi State University. He holds a Ph.D. in Computer Science, a B.S. in Computer Science from UNC Pembroke, and an MBA with a focus on Project Management from Mississippi State University. Dr. Hudson’s research focuses on advancing off-road autonomous systems, multi-agent robotics, and precision field robotics for agricultural and defense applications. His work integrates ecological simulation, machine learning, and AI to improve autonomous navigation, enhance ground vehicle mobility forecasting, and drive robust system deployment in complex, unstructured environments. He is dedicated to bridging the gap between simulation and real-world operation, developing technologies that enable reliable autonomy in GPS-denied and dynamic terrains. As an educator and mentor, he leads interdisciplinary research projects and mentors students in robotic systems development, fostering innovation at the intersection of autonomy, AI, and field robotics.

  </div>

